org.eclipse.gef4.geometry.shapes
Class Rectangle

java.lang.Object
  org.eclipse.gef4.geometry.shapes.Rectangle
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Geometry
public class Rectangle
extends Object
implements Geometry

Represents the geometric shape of a rectangle, where a rectangle is characterized by means of its upper left corner (x,y) and its size (width, height). Note that while all manipulations (e.g. within shrink, expand) within this class are based on double precision, all comparisons (e.g. within contains, intersects, equals, etc.) are based on a limited precision (with an accuracy defined within PrecisionUtils) to compensate for rounding effects.

toSWTRectangle

public Rectangle toSWTRectangle()
Converts this Rectangle into an Rectangle. Note that as Rectangle is integer-based, this implies a loss of precision. The returned rectangle is the smallest integer-precision representation that fully contains this Rectangle.

Returns:
An Rectangle representation of this Rectangle.
